developer friendly.\n\nImageCaptcha has one built-in font, DroidSansMono, which is licensed under\nApache License 2. You should always use your own fonts:\n\n```\ncaptcha = ImageCaptcha(fonts=['/path/to/A.ttf', '/path/to/B.ttf'])\n```\n\nYou can put as many fonts as you like. But be aware of your memory, all of\nthe fonts are loaded into your memory, so keep them a lot, but not too\nmany.\n\n```\nparam width\n\nThe width of the CAPTCHA image.\n\nparam height\n\nThe height of the CAPTCHA image.\n\nparam fonts\n\nFonts to be used to generate CAPTCHA images.\n\nparam font_sizes\n\nRandom choose a font size from this parameters.\n```\n"]}], "exports": [{"name": "captcha.image.ImageCaptcha", "xref": {"fqname": "captcha.image.ImageCaptcha", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "captcha.audio", "documentation": ["captcha.audio\n~~~~~~~~~~~~~\n\nGenerate Audio CAPTCHAs, with built-in digits CAPTCHA.\n\nThis module is totally inspired by https://github.com/dchest/captcha", "coding: utf-8"], "functions": [{"name": "captcha.audio._read_wave_file", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "filepath", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "bytearray", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bytearray", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "captcha.audio.change_speed", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "body", "type": {"name": "bytearray", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bytearray", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "speed", "type": {"name": "float", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.float", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "bytearray", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bytearray", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Change the voice speed of the wave body."]}, {"name": "captcha.audio.patch_wave_header", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "body", "type":